  <title>SWIG-&swig-version;</title>

  <sect2 role="package">
    <title>Introduction</title>

    <para>
      SWIG is a software development tool that connects programs written in C
      and C++ with a variety of high-level programming languages such as Perl,
      Python, Tcl and Ruby. It is most commonly used to create high-level
      interpreted or compiled programming environments, user interfaces, and as
      a tool for testing and prototyping C/C++ software. SWIG can also export
      its parse tree in the form of XML and Lisp s-expressions.
    </para>

